854 /* 64-bit types for compilers that support them, plus some obsolete variants */
855 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__arm) || defined(__IAR_SYSTEMS_ICC__) || defined(__ghs__) || defined(_WIN64)
856 typedef unsigned long long NvU64; /* 0 to 18446744073709551615 */
857 typedef long long NvS64; /* -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807 */
858 #else
859 typedef unsigned __int64 NvU64; /* 0 to 18446744073709551615 */
860 typedef __int64 NvS64; /* -9223372036854775808 to 9223372036854775807 */
861 #endif
862 
863 // mac os 32-bit still needs this
864 #if (defined(macintosh) || defined(__APPLE__)) && !defined(__LP64__)
865 typedef signed long NvS32; /* -2147483648 to 2147483647 */
866 #else
867 typedef signed int NvS32; /* -2147483648 to 2147483647 */
868 #endif
869 
870 // mac os 32-bit still needs this
871 #if ( (defined(macintosh) && defined(__LP64__) && (__NVAPI_RESERVED0__)) || \
872  (!defined(macintosh) && defined(__NVAPI_RESERVED0__)) )
873 typedef unsigned int NvU32; /* 0 to 4294967295 */
874 #else
875 typedef unsigned long NvU32; /* 0 to 4294967295 */
876 #endif

878 typedef signed short NvS16;
879 typedef unsigned short NvU16;

4946 //
4956 typedef enum
4957 {
4958  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_NONE,
4959 
4960  // 'BASIC' topos start here
4961  //
4962  // The result of using one of these Mosaic topos is that multiple monitors
4963  // will combine to create a single desktop.
4964  //
4965  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_BEGIN_BASIC,
4966  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x2_BASIC = NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_BEGIN_BASIC,
4967  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x1_BASIC,
4968  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x3_BASIC,
4969  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_3x1_BASIC,
4970  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x4_BASIC,
4971  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_4x1_BASIC,
4972  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x2_BASIC,
4973  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x3_BASIC,
4974  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x4_BASIC,
4975  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_3x2_BASIC,
4976  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_4x2_BASIC,
4977  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x5_BASIC,
4978  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x6_BASIC,
4979  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_7x1_BASIC,
4980 
4981  // Add padding for 10 more entries. 6 will be enough room to specify every
4982  // possible topology with 8 or fewer displays, so this gives us a little
4983  // extra should we need it.
4984  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_END_BASIC = NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_7x1_BASIC + 9,
4985 
4986  // 'PASSIVE_STEREO' topos start here
4987  //
4988  // The result of using one of these Mosaic topos is that multiple monitors
4989  // will combine to create a single PASSIVE STEREO desktop. What this means is
4990  // that there will be two topos that combine to create the overall desktop.
4991  // One topo will be used for the left eye, and the other topo (of the
4992  // same rows x cols), will be used for the right eye. The difference between
4993  // the two topos is that different GPUs and displays will be used.
4994  //
4995  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_BEGIN_PASSIVE_STEREO, // value shadowed in nvEscDef.h
4996  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x2_PASSIVE_STEREO = NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_BEGIN_PASSIVE_STEREO,
4997  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x1_PASSIVE_STEREO,
4998  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x3_PASSIVE_STEREO,
4999  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_3x1_PASSIVE_STEREO,
5000  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_1x4_PASSIVE_STEREO,
5001  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_4x1_PASSIVE_STEREO,
5002  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x2_PASSIVE_STEREO,
5003  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_END_PASSIVE_STEREO = NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_2x2_PASSIVE_STEREO + 4,
5004 
5005 
5006  //
5007  // Total number of topos. Always leave this at the end of the enumeration.
5008  //
5009  NV_MOSAIC_TOPO_MAX
5010 
5011 } NV_MOSAIC_TOPO;
